OL,3,CBelfast hero describes fighting off
OL,4,Cknifeman with son's hurling stick
OL,6,FMaitiu Mag Tighearnan, who fought off
OL,7,Fthe suspected knifeman, spoke to Good
OL,8,FMorning Britain about what happened
OL,10,FA man who bravely intervened in the
OL,11,FBelfast knife attack has denied his
OL,12,Factions were heroic and said it was a
OL,13,F"natural reaction" to rush to the
OL,14,Fvictim's aid.
OL,16,FMaitiu Mag Tighearnan, 32, had been in
OL,17,Fthe car with with his friend Andre on
OL,18,FMonday night, when the pair came
OL,19,Facross Stephen Ogilvie being brutally
OL,20,Fstabbed in the head and neck in the
OL,21,Fmiddle of the road in north Belfast.
OL,26,@nD@IrpnD@Trp
