OL,3,CBelfast hero describes fighting off
OL,4,Cknifeman with son's hurling stick
OL,6,FTighearnan said he knew of a family in
OL,7,Fhis area whose shop of 15 or 20 years
OL,8,Fhad been destroyed in the protests.
OL,10,F"Everybody is entitled to their right
OL,11,Fof opinion and their right to protest
OL,12,F(...) but when it turns violent, then
OL,13,Fyou lose sight of the protest and what
OL,14,Fit stands for," he told GMB.
OL,16,F"From what I sort of understood from
OL,17,Fspeaking to the shop owners, they've
OL,18,Fbeen here 30 years. Their kids went to
OL,19,Fschool here and still do, even their
OL,20,Fgrandkids were born here.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781179881
OL,3,CBelfast hero describes fighting off
OL,4,Cknifeman with son's hurling stick
OL,6,F"So what happened was, amongst
OL,7,Feverything that's happening someone
OL,8,Fhas seen someone of colour and that's
OL,9,Fled to that.
OL,11,F"We have people in our society who
OL,12,Fcontribute towards our economy, who
OL,13,Fcontribute to our country. Attacking
OL,14,Fthose people makes no sense, and then
OL,15,Fthat is where the bad of the protests
OL,16,Fcomes from."
